        <type>void</type>
        <definition>void PanelGroup::registerADC</definition>
        <argsstring>(ADS1115 &amp;adc, uint8_t addr=0x48, TwoWire &amp;wire=Wire)</argsstring>
        <name>registerADC</name>
        <qualifiedname>PanelGroup::registerADC</qualifiedname>
        <param>
          <type><ref refid="classADS1115" kindref="compound">ADS1115</ref> &amp;</type>
          <declname>adc</declname>
        </param>
        <param>
          <type>uint8_t</type>
          <declname>addr</declname>
          <defval>0x48</defval>
        </param>
        <param>
          <type>TwoWire &amp;</type>
          <declname>wire</declname>
          <defval>Wire</defval>
        </param>
        <briefdescription>
<para>Register an <ref refid="classADS1115" kindref="compound">ADS1115</ref> ADC. Call before <ref refid="namespacePanelGroup_1a54bf0702b5027fc15906ca378515ad0b" kindref="member">setup()</ref>. </para>
        </briefdescription>
        <detaileddescription>
<para><ref refid="namespacePanelGroup" kindref="compound">PanelGroup</ref> calls adc.begin(addr, wire) during <ref refid="namespacePanelGroup_1a54bf0702b5027fc15906ca378515ad0b" kindref="member">setup()</ref>. Register each <ref refid="classADS1115" kindref="compound">ADS1115</ref> instance exactly once — multiple AnalogInput objects may share the same chip.</para>
<para>Adafruit_ADS1115 takes address and bus via begin(), not the constructor. Pattern: <programlisting><codeline><highlight class="normal"><ref refid="classADS1115" kindref="compound">ADS1115</ref><sp/>adc;</highlight></codeline>
<codeline><highlight class="normal"><ref refid="namespacePanelGroup_1a524f38dd1f420a121532180a1347a5e9" kindref="member">PanelGroup::registerADC</ref>(adc,<sp/>0x48,<sp/>Wire);<sp/><sp/><sp/></highlight><highlight class="comment">//<sp/>0x48–0x4B<sp/>via<sp/>ADDR<sp/>pin</highlight></codeline>
</programlisting></para>
<para><parameterlist kind="param"><parameteritem>
<parameternamelist>
<parametername>adc</parametername>
</parameternamelist>
<parameterdescription>
<para><ref refid="classADS1115" kindref="compound">ADS1115</ref> instance. Must outlive <ref refid="namespacePanelGroup" kindref="compound">PanelGroup</ref>. </para>
</parameterdescription>
</parameteritem>
<parameteritem>
<parameternamelist>
<parametername>addr</parametername>
</parameternamelist>
<parameterdescription>
<para>I2C address (0x48–0x4B via ADDR pin). Default 0x48. </para>
</parameterdescription>
</parameteritem>
<parameteritem>
<parameternamelist>
<parametername>wire</parametername>
</parameternamelist>
<parameterdescription>
<para>I2C bus. Default Wire (I2C1 on STM32). </para>
</parameterdescription>
</parameteritem>
</parameterlist>
<simplesect kind="note"><para>Wire.begin() (or Wire1.begin()) must be called by the sketch before <ref refid="namespacePanelGroup_1a54bf0702b5027fc15906ca378515ad0b" kindref="member">setup()</ref>. </para>
</simplesect>
</para>
        </detaileddescription>
